I"W<p>Interesting times.  I still think <a href="http://flickr.com/">Flickr</a> is more compelling than <a href="http://picasa.com/google/">Picasa/Google</a> because Flickr is cross platform (Mac, PC, Linux, mobile phones), and cross blog (MovableType, TypePad, Blogware, Manila) unlike Picasa/Google</p>

<p>Google plan seems to be: offer free services that will get people to post their stuff (including email, blog text posts and blog photo posts) in order for Google to make money off of AdSense, i.e. context specific ads.</p>

